channel.title: Can anyone get this running?
channel.description:
This is a mudclient-40, I've got it running as far as I can, it's pretty cool, it has the character registration stuff ect on it. The client loads upfine, but you'll notice the errors in the cmd, It's either not loading / missing alot of entity files, but it still manages to load 115 of them ?
The weird thing that gets me is, it loads the cache, and it loads .txt files, it's like the cache has been extracted? Makes me wonder if it's modded already not sure,
But yeah if someone could get this running that'd be great. It uses an entity24.jag file I think, renamed to entity3.jag.
I've originised it alot better into folders ect,
Link: http://uppit.com/7hieoe61y896/mudclient40.rar

item.dc:creator: @dimebagx dimebagx
item.description:
@dimebagx wrote:

Awww wtf, i just wrote a server for it,
Stripped down my x-pk server,
It doesn’t handle connection reponses for some reason, but when I host
another server and connect with mc40 , i get a login response, but when trying to connect with the one
I just coded, i get that below but no login response

        if (login_ID != 2) {
            System.out.println("Login Id was " + login_ID + " but expected 10?");

I got some packets listed if you need, also done quite a bit of refactoring on the client

Edit, this is what I got up to, It should contain all the bare essentials, it logs in fine on my other clients, but mc40 wont log in,
But, there are errors with the other clients , u connect a 2nd player its just a black screen, works with 1 player… can’t walk… even though I put walking in -.-, theres somthing wrong/missing for the login handlers I think.
Anyway, heres the server, Vortex if you could take the time to figure out why mc40 won’t connect to it (it’s only 30kb src and class), that’d help me a bunch i’ve come too far on this to let it drop =\ Wasted 2-3 hours of my LIFE.
